{
  "doc_id": "39321",
  "text": "Large PAHs have a preference for the L o phase [CITATION_1] , while benzene and fullerene end up in the L d phase of phase-separating bilayers in MD simulations [CITATION_2] . This is in agreement with the localization of PAHs in DRMs measured here. The large rigid compounds induce order by forcing the acyl chains to arrange themselves around the molecule, which occurs with an entropic penalty [CITATION_3] . In the already more ordered L o phase, the costs are lower than in less ordered L d phase, hence the preference of these compounds for L o .",
